                      from the Bai-Perron Test, the UDMax and WDMax values are greater than the critical values. Therefore, the Sequential Bai-Perron Test has two significant structural breaks in the time series. Consequently, three different regimes have been identified. The first regime spans from 1990 to 1995, consisting of 6 observations. The second regime covers the period from 1996 to 2002, totaling seven observations. The third regime spans from 2003 to 2021, comprising 19 observations. In the first regime, except for the trend coefficient, both the constant and trend terms are statistically significant. The structural breaks in 1996 and 2003 are significant (see Tables 9–13




